\section{Signed directed dyads}{

The six signed directed dyads (\code{n = 2}, \code{directed}, \code{signed}) are the
Holland-Leinhardt dyad census (Null, Asymmetric, Mutual) refined by the
sign of each arc. They correspond to the dyadic reciprocity motifs of
Gallo et al. (2025) as follows:\tabular{lll}{
   \code{to_motifs()} label \tab Structure \tab Gallo et al. (2025) \cr
   \code{Null} \tab no ties \tab (empty dyad) \cr
   \verb{Asymmetric+} \tab one positive arc \tab \eqn{L^{+}_{\rightarrow}} (single positive) \cr
   \verb{Asymmetric-} \tab one negative arc \tab \eqn{L^{-}_{\rightarrow}} (single negative) \cr
   \verb{Mutual++} \tab reciprocated, both positive \tab \eqn{L^{+}_{\leftrightarrow}} (reciprocated positive) \cr
   \verb{Mutual--} \tab reciprocated, both negative \tab \eqn{L^{-}_{\leftrightarrow}} (reciprocated negative) \cr
   \verb{Mutual+-} \tab reciprocated, discordant signs \tab \eqn{L^{\pm}_{\leftrightarrow}} (reciprocated mixed) \cr
}
}

